Here is the complete implementation plan. Let me walk you through the key decisions:

---

## Plan Summary

### New package: `packages/rest-api-client-generator/`

**6 source files**, following the exact same scaffold as `client-generator-ts`:

| File | Role |
|---|---|
| `field-type-mapper.ts` | Pure lookup: `'Int' → 'number'`, `'DateTime' → 'string'`, etc. |
| `enum-builder.ts` | Uses `@prisma/ts-builders` to emit `export type Role = "USER" \| "ADMIN"` |
| `model-builder.ts` | The core — builds model interface, 4 input types, a `{Model}Delegate` interface, and a `{Model}Delegate` class with fetch-based CRUD bodies |
| `generate-client.ts` | Orchestrates all builders, assembles the final string, writes `index.ts` |
| `generator.ts` | `RestApiClientGenerator implements Generator` — mirrors `PrismaClientTsGenerator` |
| `index.ts` | Exports only the public surface |

### Generated output structure (per model)

```typescript
// Enums
export type Role = "USER" | "ADMIN"

// Model interface (all scalar fields, nullability via T | null)
export interface User { id: number; email: string; name: string | null; role: Role }

// Input types
export interface UserWhereUniqueInput { id?: number; email?: string }
export interface UserWhereInput { id?: number; email?: string | null; ... }
export interface UserCreateInput { email: string; name?: string | null; role?: Role }
// ↑ excludes: @id with hasDefaultValue, @updatedAt, relation fields, isReadOnly FK fields
export interface UserUpdateInput { email?: string; name?: string | null; ... }
// ↑ additionally excludes the @id field

// Delegate (interface + class with fetch methods)
class UserDelegate { findMany / findUnique / create / update / delete }

export class RestApiClient {
  readonly user: UserDelegate
  constructor(baseUrl = 'http://localhost:3000') { this.user = new UserDelegate(baseUrl) }
}
```

### 3 external file changes

1. `tsconfig.build.bundle.json` — add path alias
2. `packages/client-generator-registry/package.json` — add `workspace:*` dep
3. `packages/client-generator-registry/src/default.ts` — register `new RestApiClientGenerator()`

